  "texts": [
    "In perception, machines are no match for humans (Tsang and Almirall 2021).",
    "AI and robotic difficulties with perception and manipulation illustrate Moravec's paradox (Stern 2023): owing to a lack of prior knowledge (\"ground truth\"), computers excel in tasks humans find hard (math) but fail in those even toddlers find easy.",
    "Human perception requires more than just tracking objects or data (video and audio) through space and time (Patraucean et al. 2022); it's experiencing the world.",
    "Creative IntelligenceCreativity can be defined partly as the ability to produce ideas or artifacts (literature, music, paintings, sculptures, plays) that are novel or original (Boden 2003; Frey and Osborne 2017).",
    "This is often done by combining ideas or artifacts in ways not previously tried."
  ],
